Variance is not necassarily a measure of class separability!

Project on a lower dimension which is a linear combination of original features as well as contains class information.

LDA Objective

Find direction 𝑣v a linear combination of original 𝑑d features that maximizes class separability of the projected data

Projected of sample 𝑥∈ℝ𝑑x∈Rd:

𝑦=𝑣𝑇𝑥(1)(1)y=vTx

Two Classes

Class  𝝎1  with mean  𝜇1  covariance  Σ1Class  𝝎2  with mean  𝜇2  covariance  Σ2Class  ω1  with mean  μ1  covariance  Σ1Class  ω2  with mean  μ2  covariance  Σ2

Let

𝜇1~ and 𝜎1~2 be mean and variance of projected data for the points in class 𝝎1,𝜇2~ and 𝜎2~2 be mean and variance of projected data for the points in class 𝝎2.μ1~ and σ1~2 be mean and variance of projected data for the points in class ω1,μ2~ and σ2~2 be mean and variance of projected data for the points in class ω2.

Maximize Fisher Discriminant Ratio (FDR) on 𝑦y

maximize𝐹𝐷𝑅=(𝜇1~−𝜇2~)2𝜎1~2+𝜎2~2(2)(2)maximizeFDR=(μ1~−μ2~)2σ1~2+σ2~2

𝜇1~=𝑣𝑇𝜇1μ1~=vTμ1

𝜇2~=𝑣𝑇𝜇2μ2~=vTμ2

𝜎1~2=∑𝑦∈𝝎1(𝑦−𝜇1~)2=∑𝑋∈𝝎1(𝑣𝑇𝑥−𝑣𝑇𝜇1)2=∑𝑋∈𝝎1𝑣𝑇(𝑥−𝜇1)(𝑥−𝜇1)𝑇𝑣=𝑣𝑇Σ1𝑣σ1~2=∑y∈ω1(y−μ1~)2=∑X∈ω1(vTx−vTμ1)2=∑X∈ω1vT(x−μ1)(x−μ1)Tv=vTΣ1v

𝜎2~2=𝑣𝑇Σ2𝑣σ2~2=vTΣ2v

(𝜇1~−𝜇2~)2=(𝑣𝑇𝜇1−𝑣𝑇𝜇2)2=𝑣𝑇(𝜇1−𝜇2)(𝜇1−𝜇2)𝑇𝑣=𝑣𝑇𝑆𝑏𝑣(μ1~−μ2~)2=(vTμ1−vTμ2)2=vT(μ1−μ2)(μ1−μ2)Tv=vTSbv
𝜎1~2+𝜎2~2=𝑣𝑇Σ1𝑣+𝑣𝑇Σ2𝑣=𝑣𝑇𝑆𝑤𝑣σ1~2+σ2~2=vTΣ1v+vTΣ2v=vTSwv

LDA Objective

maximize(𝜇1~−𝜇2~)2𝜎1~2+𝜎2~2=𝑣𝑇𝑆𝑏𝑣𝑣𝑇𝑆𝑤𝑣≃𝑣𝑇𝑆−1𝑤𝑆𝑏𝑣(3)(3)maximize(μ1~−μ2~)2σ1~2+σ2~2=vTSbvvTSwv≃vTSw−1Sbv

Solution for 𝑣v in (3)(3) given by the eigenvector of 𝐽=𝑆−1𝑤𝑆𝑏J=Sw−1Sb corresponding largest eigenvalue.

LDA: Project 𝑋X on the eigenvectors of its covaraince matrix 𝑆−1𝑤𝑆𝑏Sw−1Sb ¶

In [37]:
N=nrow(X)
nclass=length(unique(class))
mu0<-colMeans(X)
S<-list()
Mu<-list()
Sw=0
for(i in 1:nclass)
{
    wi=X[which(class==i),]
    Ni=nrow(wi)
    Mu[[i]]<-colMeans(wi)
    S[[i]]<-cov(wi)
    cat("\n\n Class ",i,": ")
    cat("\n Mean Mu: ",Mu[[i]])
    cat("\n Covariance Matrix: \n")
    print(S[[i]])
    Sw=Sw+S[[i]]
}
MuDiff=Mu[[1]]-Mu[[2]]
Sb=outer(MuDiff,MuDiff)
cat("\n Within cluster scatter Sw: \n")
print(Sw)
cat("\n Between cluster scatter Sb: \n")
print(Sb)

Eigenvalues of 𝐽J

maximize𝑣𝑇𝐽𝑣(3)(3)maximizevTJv

𝐽=𝑆−1𝑤𝑆𝑏 J=Sw−1Sb  where  𝑆𝑏=(𝜇1−𝜇2)(𝜇1−𝜇2)𝑇 Sb=(μ1−μ2)(μ1−μ2)T

Rank of 𝑆𝑏Sb is 1 (outer product of two vectors).

Rank of 𝐽J is also atmost 1, so atmost 1 eigenvalue of 𝐽J will be non-zero.

𝜆2(𝐽)=0λ2(J)=0

For 𝑀M classes

Between-class scatter matrix

𝑆𝑏=∑𝑖=1𝑀𝑃(𝝎𝑖)(𝜇𝑖−𝜇0)(𝜇𝑖−𝜇0)𝑇(4)(4)Sb=∑i=1MP(ωi)(μi−μ0)(μi−μ0)T
𝑆𝑏Sb is the sum of 𝑀M matrices of rank ≤1≤1.

Additional constraint on mean 𝜇𝑖μi:

𝜇0=1𝑀∑𝑖=1𝑀𝜇𝑖μ0=1M∑i=1Mμi

Rank of 𝑆𝑏Sb is atmost (𝑀−1)(M−1), atmost (𝑀−1)(M−1) eigenvalues of 𝐽J will be non-zero.

LDA extracts atmost (𝑀−1)(M−1) components.

First LDA component

𝑦=𝑋𝑣(4)(4)y=Xv

In [41]:
N=nrow(X)
nclass=length(unique(class))
mu0<-colMeans(X)
cat("\n Global mean: ", mu0)
S<-list()
Mu<-list()
P<-list()
for(i in 1:nclass)
{
    wi=X[which(class==i),]
    Ni=nrow(wi)
    P[[i]]<-Ni/N
    Mu[[i]]<-colMeans(wi)
    S[[i]]<-cov(wi)
    cat("\n\n Class ",i,": ")
    cat("\n Prior P: ",P[[i]])
    cat("\n Mean Mu: ",Mu[[i]])
    cat("\n Covariance Matrix: \n")
    print(S[[i]])
}
Sw=0
Sb=0
for(i in 1:nclass)
{
    mui0=Mu[[i]]-mu0
    Sw=Sw+ P[[i]]*S[[i]]
    Sb=Sb+ P[[i]]*outer(mui0,mui0)
}
